.TH "mpvc" "1" "April, 2026" ""
.SH NAME
mpvc \- mpc\-like command\-line control interface for mpv
.SH SYNOPSIS
mpvc options [file|url|playlist|\-]
.SH DESCRIPTION
mpvc is a command\-line utility that provides mpc\-like control over the
mpv media player.
It allows users to manage playback, control volume, add and remove media
from the playlist, and display playlist information through a simple
command\-line interface.
.PP
The tool communicates with mpv via a Unix socket, enabling remote
control of playback without direct interaction with the mpv window.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Playback Control
.TP
\f[CR]\-P\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-play\f[R]
Start playback of the current media.
.TP
\f[CR]\-p\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-toggle\f[R]
Toggle between play and pause states.
.TP
\f[CR]\-s\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-stop\f[R]
Stop playback completely.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-next\f[R]
Jump to the next entry in the playlist.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-prev\f[R]
Jump to the previous entry in the playlist.
.SS Playlist Management
.TP
\f[CR]\-a\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-add FILE\f[R]
Add a file or URL to the playlist.
Supports local files, YouTube URLs, and other media sources.
.TP
\f[CR]\-r\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-remove ID\f[R]
Remove a playlist entry by its numeric ID.
.TP
\f[CR]\-i\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-playlist\f[R]
Display the current playlist with filenames truncated to fit terminal
width.
.TP
\f[CR]\-I\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-fullplaylist\f[R]
Display the complete current playlist with full filenames.
.SS Loop and Repeat Modes
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-repeat\f[R]
Enable loop mode for the entire playlist.
Playback will restart from the beginning after reaching the end.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-single\f[R]
Enable single\-file loop mode.
The current file will repeat indefinitely.
.SS Volume Control
.TP
\f[CR]\-v\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-vol [+\-]N\f[R]
Adjust volume by the specified amount.
Use +N to increase or \-N to decrease volume.
Without an argument, displays current volume.
.SS Information and Help
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Display short help message with basic usage information.
.TP
\f[CR]\-H\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\-long\f[R]
Display detailed help message with all available options and examples.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a file to the playlist:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-a /path/to/song.mp3
.EE
.PP
Toggle playback:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-p
.EE
.PP
Increase volume by 5:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-v +5
.EE
.PP
Decrease volume by 10:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-v \-10
.EE
.PP
Display current playlist:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-i
.EE
.PP
Jump to next track:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-\-next
.EE
.PP
Stop playback:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-s
.EE
.PP
Enable repeat mode:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-\-repeat
.EE
.PP
Remove track with ID 3:
.IP
.EX
mpvc \-r 3
.EE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
MPV_SOCKET
Path to the mpv Unix socket.
If not set, mpvc will attempt to locate the default socket
automatically.
.SH FILES
.TP
\(ti/.config/mpv/mpv.conf
Main mpv configuration file.
.TP
\(ti/.config/mpvc/mpvc.conf
mpvc\-specific configuration file.
.TP
\(ti/.config/mpvc/yt\-dlp.conf
Configuration for yt\-dlp integration.
